definitions.definition: The early period of the Roman Empire , during which some characteristics of the government of the Roman Republic were retained; the reign of any particular emperor during said period.
The office of one who is principal or preeminent (such as a prince ); the quality or status of being principal ; preeminence .
A state ruled by a prince ; a principality .
